{"questionId":"22594191","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, by integrating both sides of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>, show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> is an arbitrary positive constant.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone the absence of '<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>' and the modulus sign throughout.</p>\n<p>Only award the second <em><strong>A</strong></em> mark if the constant of integration has been dealt with correctly.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone the absence of '<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi></math>' when awarding the first <em><strong>A</strong></em> mark.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi>C</mi></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi>C</mi></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone the absence of '<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi></math>' when awarding the first <em><strong>A</strong></em> mark.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi>C</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone the absence of '<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>' throughout.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>Integrating factor:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mo>d</mo><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22594191","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ2.1c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, by integrating both sides of f'xfx=g'xg'x-gx, show that fx=Ae∫g'xg'x-gxdx, where A is an arbitrary positive constant.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.10—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.16—Integration by substitution, parts and repeated parts"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}